{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013AtVNrbKdya5mTb28jWqN6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: 001 Coinflip\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Ideation | Complete |\n     9→| Priority | P0 |\n    10→| Phase | 1 |\n    11→| NR_OF_TRIES | 10 |\n    12→\n    13→---\n    14→\n    15→## Overview\n    16→\n    17→Coinflip is the simplest game on the platform and the first end-to-end delivery target. Two players wager equal amounts in a 1v1 match. A verifiable random function determines one winner who takes the entire pot minus the platform fee. It validates the full wager-to-settlement flow before Crash development begins.\n    18→\n    19→## User Stories\n    20→\n    21→- As a player, I want to create a coinflip match by choosing a tier and side so that I can challenge an opponent at stakes I'm comfortable with.\n    22→- As a player, I want to browse open coinflip lobbies so that I can join a match quickly.\n    23→- As a player, I want to see a fair coin flip animation and result so that I trust the outcome is legitimate.\n    24→- As a winner, I want my payout settled on-chain so that I can claim my winnings trustlessly.\n    25→- As a player, I want to verify the fairness of any completed match so that I can confirm the result was not manipulated.\n    26→\n    27→---\n    28→\n    29→## Scope Alignment\n    30→\n    31→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (Product Scope - V1 In Scope: Coinflip), Section 5 (V1 Game Scope - Coinflip), Section 8 (Delivery Plan - Phase 1)\n    32→- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n    33→- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n    34→\n    35→## Required Context Files\n    36→\n    37→- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/COINFLIP.md` (game concept source)\n    38→- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/PLATFORM.md` (tier-based betting, platform fee, provably fair system)\n    39→- `docs/SCOPE.md` (scope boundary and shared game requirements)\n    40→\n    41→## Contract Files\n    42→\n    43→### Frontend (Existing UI — preserve design/UX)\n    44→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state management\n    45→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/components/` — ActiveMatchView, CoinAnimation, CoinSideSelector, MatchCard, OpenMatchesList\n    46→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — frontend type definitions\n    47→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/mock-simulation.ts` — mock to be replaced with real chain calls\n    48→\n    49→### Game Engine (TS instruction builders)\n    50→- `packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts` — PDA derivation, instruction builders, payout calc\n    51→- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — shared types + fee constants\n    52→- `packages/game-engine/src/payouts.ts` — payout math\n    53→\n    54→### On-Chain (Anchor programs — current implementation)\n    55→- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — Coinflip program (VRF rewrite pending — will use shared crate + Orao per 004 spec)\n    56→- `solana/programs/platform/` — Platform program (player profiles, fee config)\n    57→- `solana/shared/` — Shared Rust lib (fees, tiers, constants — expanding per 004 spec)\n    58→\n    59→---\n    60→\n    61→## Functional Requirements\n    62→\n    63→### FR-1: Match Creation\n    64→\n    65→A player can create a new coinflip match by selecting a betting tier (Iron through Diamond) and a side (Heads or Tails). The match appears in the open games list for other players to join.\n    66→\n    67→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    68→- [x] Player can select one of six tiers (Iron 0.005, Bronze 0.01, Silver 0.1, Gold 0.25, Platinum 0.5, Diamond 1 SOL) <!-- satisfied: shared/src/tiers.rs:5 TIER_AMOUNTS, types.ts:25 TIER_AMOUNTS_LAMPORTS, CoinflipPage TierSelector -->\n    69→- [x] Player can choose Heads or Tails <!-- satisfied: shared/src/constants.rs:2-3 SIDE_HEADS/TAILS, CoinSideSelector.tsx:19 -->\n    70→- [x] Created match appears in the lobby browser with creator name, tier, wager amount, and side chosen <!-- satisfied: MatchCard.tsx:13 (PlayerAvatar, tier, amount, side), chain.ts:139 fetchAllOpenMatches -->\n    71→- [x] Match creation requires a connected wallet with sufficient balance <!-- satisfied: CoinflipContext.tsx:169 createMatch, error.rs:19 InsufficientFunds -->\n    72→- [x] Only one active match per player at a time (enforced on-chain via PDA constraint) <!-- satisfied: state.rs:20 CoinflipMatch seeds [\"match\", creator], Anchor init constraint -->\n    73→\n    74→### FR-2: Match Joining\n    75→\n    76→A second player can join an open match. The joiner is automatically assigned the opposite side. Both players must wager the same tier amount.\n    77→\n    78→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    79→- [x] Player can browse open matches filtered by tier and sorted by newest/oldest <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:43 tier filter, :18 sortMatches (newest/oldest/amount) -->\n    80→- [x] Joining assigns the opposite side automatically <!-- satisfied: join_match.rs:25, chain.ts:122-123 onChainMatchToUI -->\n    81→- [x] Both players' wagers are equal (tier-enforced) <!-- satisfied: create_match.rs:28 entry_amount from tier, join_match.rs:25 same amount -->\n    82→- [x] Tier selection is locked once the bet is placed <!-- satisfied: state.rs:20 CoinflipMatch.tier immutable after creation -->\n    83→- [x] Join requires connected wallet with sufficient balance <!-- satisfied: CoinflipContext.tsx:206 joinMatch, chain.ts:241 buildJoinMatchTx -->\n    84→\n    85→### FR-3: Flip Resolution\n    86→\n    87→Once both players have joined, a coin flip occurs using VRF. The flip animation plays for approximately 3 seconds, then the result is revealed.\n    88→\n    89→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    90→- [x] Flip begins immediately when both players are committed <!-- satisfied: join_match.rs embeds Orao VRF request CPI, frontend polls until randomness fulfilled (spec 004 rewrite) -->\n    91→- [x] VRF determines the outcome (Heads or Tails) <!-- satisfied: Orao VRF integrated via shared vrf_orao module, claim_payout reads randomness + derives winner (spec 004 rewrite) -->\n    92→- [x] Result is deterministic and reproducible from the VRF seed <!-- satisfied: from_randomness(byte) is pure deterministic; Orao randomness account persists on-chain for proof; verification UI planned (Phase 2) -->\n    93→- [x] Flip animation plays with coin rotation and landing <!-- satisfied: CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform, spinning-heads/spinning-tails classes -->\n    94→\n    95→### FR-4: Settlement and Payout\n    96→\n    97→The winner receives the total pool minus the platform fee. Settlement is recorded on-chain. Either player (winner or loser) can trigger settlement to close the match.\n    98→\n    99→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   100→- [x] Winner payout = total_pool x 0.97 (3% platform fee) <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs:55, fees.rs:5 TOTAL_FEE_BPS=300, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n   101→- [x] Platform fee is collected to treasury PDA <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs treasury transfer, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n   102→- [x] Payout eligibility is recorded on-chain <!-- satisfied: state.rs winner+claimed fields, claim_payout CPI to update_player_profile -->\n   103→- [x] Winner can claim funds successfully <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs:55, CoinflipContext.tsx:268, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n   104→- [x] Either player can trigger settlement (loser is not blocked) <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs caller validated as creator OR opponent, payout always goes to winner -->\n   105→- [x] Settlement is idempotent (cannot double-settle) <!-- satisfied: error.rs AlreadyClaimed, test coinflip.ts:617 \"rejects double claim\" -->\n   106→- [x] Replay protection for signed actions <!-- satisfied: match account closed after claim, Anchor tx signature dedup -->\n   107→\n   108→### FR-4b: Cancellation and Refunds\n   109→\n   110→All cancellations refund deposited amounts in full. No platform fee is kept on cancellation.\n   111→\n   112→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   113→- [x] Creator can cancel a match in WAITING phase (before opponent joins) <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs, phase==WAITING check -->\n   114→- [x] Cancel refunds full entry amount + rent to creator <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs close=creator, all lamports returned -->\n   115→- [x] Timeout cancel refunds both players if VRF does not resolve within 2 minutes <!-- satisfied: timeout_cancel.rs, entry_amount refunded to each player -->\n   116→- [x] No platform fee is deducted on any cancellation <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs and timeout_cancel.rs have no fee calculation -->\n   117→- [x] Either player can trigger timeout cancel <!-- satisfied: timeout_cancel.rs caller == creator OR opponent -->\n   118→\n   119→### FR-5: Fairness Verification\n   120→\n   121→Players can verify the outcome of any completed match by inspecting the VRF inputs and recalculating the result.\n   122→\n   123→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   124→- [ ] Completed match displays VRF seed/proof details <!-- planned: MatchSettled event includes randomness bytes; Phase 2 adds vrf_request_key to event, verification UI reads Orao account -->\n   125→- [ ] Players can independently verify the result matches the VRF output <!-- planned: Phase 2 verification.ts re-derives result from Orao randomness bytes via from_randomness -->\n   126→- [ ] Verification is accessible from match history and result screen <!-- planned: Phase 2 verification UI accessible from ActiveMatchView + /fairness link -->\n   127→\n   128→### FR-6: Lobby Browser UI\n   129→\n   130→A browsable list of open coinflip matches with filtering and creation controls.\n   131→\n   132→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   133→- [x] Open games list shows creator name/avatar, tier, wager amount, side, and join button <!-- satisfied: MatchCard.tsx:13 (PlayerAvatar:25, tier:50, amount:41, side:36, join:57) -->\n   134→- [x] Filter by tier <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:43 matches.filter(m => m.tier === selectedTier) -->\n   135→- [x] Sort by newest/oldest/amount <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:18 sortMatches, :79 sort dropdown -->\n   136→- [x] Create Game panel with tier selection grid and Heads/Tails toggle <!-- satisfied: CoinflipPage.tsx sidebar TierSelector + CoinSideSelector.tsx:19 -->\n   137→- [ ] Estimated wait time shown (derived from recent match fill rate — deferred to post-MVP polish if data unavailable) <!-- deferred: self-deferred in criterion text, no match fill-rate data available -->\n   138→\n   139→### FR-7: Active Game and Result UI\n   140→\n   141→The in-match view showing both players, coin flip animation, and result.\n   142→\n   143→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   144→- [x] Both players shown with avatars, names, and wager amounts <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:88-108 PlayerAvatarCompact, side labels, entry amount -->\n   145→- [x] 3D coin flip animation with multiple rotations and gradual slowdown <!-- satisfied: CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform (front/back faces :53-58), spinning classes :43-45 -->\n   146→- [x] Winning side highlighted with glow effect <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:200-205 result color + textShadow glow -->\n   147→- [x] \"YOU WIN!\" or \"YOU LOSE\" overlay displayed <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:128 \"You Won!\", :129-139 \"You Lost\" with heart+shards animation -->\n   148→- [x] Payout amount shown for winner <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:207-210 match.payoutAmount.toFixed(4) SOL -->\n   149→- [ ] Quick rematch option available after result <!-- planned: Phase 2 rematch button in ActiveMatchView, reuses createMatch with same tier/side -->\n   150→\n   151→### FR-8: Audio Feedback\n   152→\n   153→Sound effects accompany the coinflip experience.\n   154→\n   155→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   156→- [ ] Coin flip spinning sound during animation <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n   157→- [ ] Dramatic pause before landing <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n   158→- [ ] Victory sound for winner <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n   159→- [ ] Coin clink on landing <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n   160→\n   161→---\n   162→\n   163→## Success Criteria\n   164→\n   165→- A player can create a match, have it joined, see the flip, and receive payout in a single uninterrupted flow\n   166→- Settlement correctness: winner always receives exactly (pool x 0.97), fee always reaches treasury\n   167→- Any completed match can be independently verified for fairness\n   168→- Match creation to resolution completes within 10 seconds of both players joining\n   169→- Error states (insufficient balance, network failure, wallet disconnect) are clearly communicated\n   170→\n   171→---\n   172→\n   173→## Dependencies\n   174→\n   175→- Wallet connection via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (Privy removed)\n   176→- Coinflip Anchor program (`solana/programs/coinflip`) with VRF provider (Orao, per `004-shared-infrastructure` spec)\n   177→- Platform Anchor program (`solana/programs/platform`) for player profiles + fee config\n   178→- `packages/anchor-client/` (generated from IDL via `scripts/sync-idl`)\n   179→- Shared UI components (`packages/ui/`) for buttons, modals, cards, toasts\n   180→- Dev environment: Anchor CLI 0.32.1, Solana CLI 2.3.13, Rust toolchain\n   181→\n   182→## Assumptions\n   183→\n   184→- Tier amounts are fixed at the values defined in PLATFORM.md\n   185→- Platform fee is 3% (300 bps). Confirmed in `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` §8. Split: 200 bps revenue, 70 bps rakeback, 30 bps chest treasury.\n   186→- VRF provider: Orao (per `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md` FR-4). MagicBlock VRF dropped.\n   187→- Non-custodial wallet flow via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (no Privy, no internal balance model)\n   188→- Existing on-chain programs are legacy — coinflip will be rewritten against new shared crate + chosen VRF provider (see `004-shared-infrastructure` spec)\n   189→\n   190→---\n   191→\n   192→## Validation Plan\n   193→\n   194→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   195→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   196→| 1 | Match creation with tier + side | Create match via UI, verify lobby listing | Screenshot of lobby with new match |\n   197→| 2 | Match joining assigns opposite side | Join match, verify side assignment | Screenshot showing both players |\n   198→| 3 | VRF determines outcome | Inspect VRF output, verify determinism | VRF proof + recalculated result |\n   199→| 4 | Winner payout = pool x 0.97 | Check on-chain settlement transaction | Explorer link showing amounts |\n   200→| 5 | Platform fee reaches treasury | Check treasury PDA balance | Explorer link showing fee transfer |\n   201→| 6 | Settlement is idempotent | Attempt double-settle, verify rejection | Error response or no-op proof |\n   202→| 7 | Fairness verification works | Use verification UI to recalculate result | Screenshot of verification view |\n   203→| 8 | End-to-end flow completes | Full playthrough from create to claim | Video or step-by-step screenshots |\n   204→\n   205→---\n   206→\n   207→## Completion Signal\n   208→\n   209→### Implementation Checklist\n   210→\n   211→**Phase 1: Core Implementation (complete)**\n   212→- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipConfig PDA + initialize_config instruction (done: TDD stubs commit)\n   213→- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipMatch state + create_match instruction with tier validation + escrow (done: TDD stubs commit)\n   214→- [x] [on-chain] Align shared crate tiers with spec: 6 tiers Iron→Diamond, amounts match 0.005→1.0 SOL (done: iteration 1)\n   215→- [x] [on-chain] Implement join_match — phase check, opponent != creator, escrow transfer, set LOCKED (done: iteration 2)\n   216→- [x] [on-chain] Implement resolve_match — oracle authority check, randomness→winner derivation (done: iteration 3; NOTE: deleted in 004 rewrite, replaced by claim-time VRF read)\n   217→- [x] [on-chain] Implement claim_payout — settlement, fee transfer, profile CPI, either-player trigger (done: iteration 4)\n   218→- [x] [on-chain] Implement cancel_match — WAITING-only, full refund + close (done: iteration 5)\n   219→- [x] [on-chain] Platform program scaffold — PlatformConfig + PlayerProfile + instructions (done: iteration 6)\n   220→- [x] [on-chain] CPI from coinflip claim_payout → platform update_player_profile (done: iteration 7)\n   221→- [x] [engine] Create anchor-client package + sync-idl script (done: iteration 1, engine phase)\n   222→- [x] [engine] Align game-engine with on-chain — types.ts side values, coinflip.ts PDA rewrite (done: iteration 7)\n   223→- [x] [frontend] Wire CoinflipContext to anchor-client — delete mock-simulation.ts, real chain calls (done: iteration 8)\n   224→- [x] [frontend] Wire lobby browser + error handling (done: iteration 9)\n   225→\n   226→**Phase 1b: Shared Infrastructure Rewrite (complete — spec 004)**\n   227→- [x] [on-chain] Orao VRF integration — join_match embeds VRF request, claim_payout reads randomness at claim time (done: spec 004)\n   228→- [x] [on-chain] resolve_match deleted — 3-tx flow: create→join(+VRF)→claim(+settle) (done: spec 004)\n   229→- [x] [on-chain] Shared crate modules: lifecycle, timeout, escrow, fees, pause, vrf_orao, commit_reveal, cpi (done: spec 004)\n   230→- [x] [on-chain] timeout_cancel + force_close instructions (done: spec 004)\n   231→- [x] [engine] IDL re-synced for rewritten programs (done: spec 004)\n   232→- [x] [frontend] chain.ts rewritten for Orao VRF account structures (done: spec 004)\n   233→\n   234→**Phase 2: Data Consistency**\n   235→- [x] [engine] Fix tier naming and amounts — in `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`: rename `Tier` union member `\"emerald\"` → `\"platinum\"`, update `TIER_AMOUNTS` values to SOL `{iron: 0.005, bronze: 0.01, silver: 0.1, gold: 0.25, platinum: 0.5, diamond: 1.0}`. Propagate `\"emerald\"` → `\"platinum\"` rename to ALL consumers across the monorepo (16 files reference \"emerald\" — use typecheck errors to find them all: `chain.ts`, `index.css`, boss-raid, lord-of-rngs, game-of-trades, crypto-crash, player-profile features). Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass across all packages. (done: iteration 10)\n   236→- [ ] [frontend] Verify tier display correctness after amounts fix — confirm CoinflipPage TierSelector shows SOL values `{0.005, 0.01, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1.0}`, MatchCard displays correct wager amounts, `chain.ts` `entryAmountSol` reads correct values. Fix any hardcoded tier amount references that don't flow from `TIER_AMOUNTS`. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds for platform app.\n   237→\n   238→**Phase 2: Claimable Matches (G-1)**\n   239→- [ ] [frontend] Add `fetchClaimableMatches(connection, playerPubkey)` to `features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — use `getProgramAccounts` with memcmp filters for matches where player is `creator` OR `opponent`, `claimed == false`, phase is non-terminal. Must handle both cases (player as creator and player as opponent are separate queries since the pubkey is at different offsets). Return `UIMatch[]`. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes.\n   240→- [ ] [frontend] Surface claimable matches in CoinflipContext + CoinflipPage — add `claimableMatches: UIMatch[]` to context state, poll via `fetchClaimableMatches` alongside open matches. Show \"Your Matches\" section in CoinflipPage above the open lobby list with claim/cancel actions per match. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds.\n   241→\n   242→**Phase 2: Fairness Verification (FR-5)**\n   243→- [ ] [on-chain] Add `vrf_request_key: Pubkey` field to `MatchSettled` event — in `solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` (event definition) and `claim_payout.rs` (emit site), add `vrf_request_key` from `coinflip_match.vrf_request_key`. This enables verification UIs to look up the Orao randomness account and confirm the randomness bytes are genuine VRF output. Verify: `anchor build -p coinflip` succeeds + all bankrun tests pass.\n   244→- [ ] [engine] Re-sync IDL after MatchSettled event change — run `./scripts/sync-idl` to copy updated IDL + types into `packages/anchor-client/`. Verify anchor-client exports include `vrf_request_key` in MatchSettled event type. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes across monorepo.\n   245→- [ ] [frontend] Build fairness verification utility — create `features/coinflip/utils/verification.ts`. Export `verifyMatch(connection, claimTxSignature): Promise<VerificationResult>`. Logic: (1) fetch parsed transaction by signature, (2) extract `MatchSettled` event from logs (parse program event data), (3) read `randomness` bytes from event, (4) re-derive result via `from_randomness(randomness[0])`, (5) compare derived winner to event `winner` field, (6) fetch Orao randomness account by `vrf_request_key` to confirm VRF fulfillment. Return `{verified, creator, opponent, winner, randomnessHex, derivedResult, vrfFulfilled}`. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes.\n   246→- [ ] [frontend] Build fairness verification UI — add \"Verify Fairness\" button to ActiveMatchView (visible in completed phase). Opens a verification panel/modal showing: claim tx signature, VRF request key, raw randomness hex, derived result (Heads/Tails), recorded winner, verification status badge (Verified/Failed/Pending). Also wire the existing `/fairness` link in CoinflipPage to use this verification flow (user pastes a tx signature to verify any match). Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds.\n   247→\n   248→**Phase 2: Quick Rematch (FR-7.6)**\n   249→- [ ] [frontend] Add rematch button to ActiveMatchView — visible when match phase is `complete`. Clicking calls `createMatch` with the same tier and the player's original side choice. Creates a new open match in the lobby — the opponent must find and join it manually (no forced rematch). Button text: \"Play Again\". Reuses the existing `createMatch` context action. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds.\n   250→\n   251→**Phase 2: Validation & Cleanup**\n   252→- [ ] [test] Validate carry-forward invariants against post-004 code — read and verify: (a) `vrf_request_key` is stored on `CoinflipMatch` state and now emitted in `MatchSettled` event, (b) `from_randomness()` in `shared/src/constants.rs` is pure deterministic (same byte → same side, every time), (c) `timeout_cancel` uses `shared::timeout::is_expired()` + `shared::vrf_orao::is_fulfilled()` guard, (d) `join_match` rejects non-WAITING phase, `claim_payout` rejects `claimed==true` (idempotency), (e) `create_match` calls `shared::pause::check_not_paused()`, VRF unfulfilled → claim rejects. Log each finding with file:line evidence in `docs/specs/001-coinflip/history.md`. Verify: all bankrun tests pass.\n   253→- [ ] [frontend] Remove dead code — delete unused `buildCreateMatchInstruction` export from `chain.ts` (only `buildCreateMatchTx` is used). Remove stale \"Simplified match type for UI/mock mode\" comment from `types.ts`. Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass.\n   254→- [ ] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry.\n   255→- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for coinflip pages. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures from tier name/amount changes. Then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate:\n   256→  - **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent, only expected areas changed) → commit updated baselines\n   257→  - **REVIEW** (changes look plausible but unexpected areas also changed, or uncertain) → do NOT commit baselines. Save the diff images from `test-results/` to `docs/specs/001-coinflip/visual-review/`, describe concerns in `history.md`, output `<blocker>Visual review needed: [describe what looks off]</blocker>`\n   258→  - **FAIL** (layout broken, elements missing, clearly wrong) → fix the code, do NOT update baselines\n   259→\n   260→### Scope Decisions\n   261→\n   262→- **Tiers**: On-chain canonical (Iron→Diamond, 0.005→1.0 SOL). Game-engine types.ts to be aligned (Phase 2 item). Rename \"emerald\" → \"platinum\" platform-wide.\n   263→- **Side discriminants**: 0/1 canonical (heads=0, tails=1).\n   264→- **VRF**: Orao integration complete (spec 004). Mock-vrf feature for bankrun tests. 3-tx flow: create→join(+VRF request)→claim(+VRF read+settle).\n   265→- **Platform program**: Included with CPI for player profile updates on settlement.\n   266→- **Fairness verification**: Event-based approach — MatchSettled event (with randomness + vrf_request_key) + Orao randomness account lookup. No match PDA persistence needed.\n   267→- **Deferred**: Audio integration (all 4 FR-8 items → dedicated audio spec), estimated wait time (FR-6.5 → requires match fill-rate analytics infrastructure).\n   268→\n   269→### Iteration Instructions\n   270→\n   271→Each checklist item is one autonomous iteration (`claude -p` invocation). The agent:\n   272→1. Reads this spec + history.md for prior context\n   273→2. Implements the next unchecked item\n   274→3. Runs the verification command specified in the item\n   275→4. If verification passes → checks the box, commits, outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   276→5. If verification fails → outputs `<blocker>description</blocker>` and exits\n   277→\n   278→**Only when ALL items are checked, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   279→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"394db446-9d72-42e7-88ec-8467376c4aa2","uuid":"34d9739f-1112-4597-b360-6b16b6c7b3be","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/001-coinflip/spec.md","content":"# Specification: 001 Coinflip\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Ideation | Complete |\n| Priority | P0 |\n| Phase | 1 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 10 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nCoinflip is the simplest game on the platform and the first end-to-end delivery target. Two players wager equal amounts in a 1v1 match. A verifiable random function determines one winner who takes the entire pot minus the platform fee. It validates the full wager-to-settlement flow before Crash development begins.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to create a coinflip match by choosing a tier and side so that I can challenge an opponent at stakes I'm comfortable with.\n- As a player, I want to browse open coinflip lobbies so that I can join a match quickly.\n- As a player, I want to see a fair coin flip animation and result so that I trust the outcome is legitimate.\n- As a winner, I want my payout settled on-chain so that I can claim my winnings trustlessly.\n- As a player, I want to verify the fairness of any completed match so that I can confirm the result was not manipulated.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (Product Scope - V1 In Scope: Coinflip), Section 5 (V1 Game Scope - Coinflip), Section 8 (Delivery Plan - Phase 1)\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/COINFLIP.md` (game concept source)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/PLATFORM.md` (tier-based betting, platform fee, provably fair system)\n- `docs/SCOPE.md` (scope boundary and shared game requirements)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n### Frontend (Existing UI — preserve design/UX)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state management\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/components/` — ActiveMatchView, CoinAnimation, CoinSideSelector, MatchCard, OpenMatchesList\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — frontend type definitions\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/mock-simulation.ts` — mock to be replaced with real chain calls\n\n### Game Engine (TS instruction builders)\n- `packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts` — PDA derivation, instruction builders, payout calc\n- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — shared types + fee constants\n- `packages/game-engine/src/payouts.ts` — payout math\n\n### On-Chain (Anchor programs — current implementation)\n- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — Coinflip program (VRF rewrite pending — will use shared crate + Orao per 004 spec)\n- `solana/programs/platform/` — Platform program (player profiles, fee config)\n- `solana/shared/` — Shared Rust lib (fees, tiers, constants — expanding per 004 spec)\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Match Creation\n\nA player can create a new coinflip match by selecting a betting tier (Iron through Diamond) and a side (Heads or Tails). The match appears in the open games list for other players to join.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Player can select one of six tiers (Iron 0.005, Bronze 0.01, Silver 0.1, Gold 0.25, Platinum 0.5, Diamond 1 SOL) <!-- satisfied: shared/src/tiers.rs:5 TIER_AMOUNTS, types.ts:25 TIER_AMOUNTS_LAMPORTS, CoinflipPage TierSelector -->\n- [x] Player can choose Heads or Tails <!-- satisfied: shared/src/constants.rs:2-3 SIDE_HEADS/TAILS, CoinSideSelector.tsx:19 -->\n- [x] Created match appears in the lobby browser with creator name, tier, wager amount, and side chosen <!-- satisfied: MatchCard.tsx:13 (PlayerAvatar, tier, amount, side), chain.ts:139 fetchAllOpenMatches -->\n- [x] Match creation requires a connected wallet with sufficient balance <!-- satisfied: CoinflipContext.tsx:169 createMatch, error.rs:19 InsufficientFunds -->\n- [x] Only one active match per player at a time (enforced on-chain via PDA constraint) <!-- satisfied: state.rs:20 CoinflipMatch seeds [\"match\", creator], Anchor init constraint -->\n\n### FR-2: Match Joining\n\nA second player can join an open match. The joiner is automatically assigned the opposite side. Both players must wager the same tier amount.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Player can browse open matches filtered by tier and sorted by newest/oldest <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:43 tier filter, :18 sortMatches (newest/oldest/amount) -->\n- [x] Joining assigns the opposite side automatically <!-- satisfied: join_match.rs:25, chain.ts:122-123 onChainMatchToUI -->\n- [x] Both players' wagers are equal (tier-enforced) <!-- satisfied: create_match.rs:28 entry_amount from tier, join_match.rs:25 same amount -->\n- [x] Tier selection is locked once the bet is placed <!-- satisfied: state.rs:20 CoinflipMatch.tier immutable after creation -->\n- [x] Join requires connected wallet with sufficient balance <!-- satisfied: CoinflipContext.tsx:206 joinMatch, chain.ts:241 buildJoinMatchTx -->\n\n### FR-3: Flip Resolution\n\nOnce both players have joined, a coin flip occurs using VRF. The flip animation plays for approximately 3 seconds, then the result is revealed.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Flip begins immediately when both players are committed <!-- satisfied: join_match.rs embeds Orao VRF request CPI, frontend polls until randomness fulfilled (spec 004 rewrite) -->\n- [x] VRF determines the outcome (Heads or Tails) <!-- satisfied: Orao VRF integrated via shared vrf_orao module, claim_payout reads randomness + derives winner (spec 004 rewrite) -->\n- [x] Result is deterministic and reproducible from the VRF seed <!-- satisfied: from_randomness(byte) is pure deterministic; Orao randomness account persists on-chain for proof; verification UI planned (Phase 2) -->\n- [x] Flip animation plays with coin rotation and landing <!-- satisfied: CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform, spinning-heads/spinning-tails classes -->\n\n### FR-4: Settlement and Payout\n\nThe winner receives the total pool minus the platform fee. Settlement is recorded on-chain. Either player (winner or loser) can trigger settlement to close the match.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Winner payout = total_pool x 0.97 (3% platform fee) <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs:55, fees.rs:5 TOTAL_FEE_BPS=300, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n- [x] Platform fee is collected to treasury PDA <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs treasury transfer, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n- [x] Payout eligibility is recorded on-chain <!-- satisfied: state.rs winner+claimed fields, claim_payout CPI to update_player_profile -->\n- [x] Winner can claim funds successfully <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs:55, CoinflipContext.tsx:268, test coinflip.ts:575 -->\n- [x] Either player can trigger settlement (loser is not blocked) <!-- satisfied: claim_payout.rs caller validated as creator OR opponent, payout always goes to winner -->\n- [x] Settlement is idempotent (cannot double-settle) <!-- satisfied: error.rs AlreadyClaimed, test coinflip.ts:617 \"rejects double claim\" -->\n- [x] Replay protection for signed actions <!-- satisfied: match account closed after claim, Anchor tx signature dedup -->\n\n### FR-4b: Cancellation and Refunds\n\nAll cancellations refund deposited amounts in full. No platform fee is kept on cancellation.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Creator can cancel a match in WAITING phase (before opponent joins) <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs, phase==WAITING check -->\n- [x] Cancel refunds full entry amount + rent to creator <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs close=creator, all lamports returned -->\n- [x] Timeout cancel refunds both players if VRF does not resolve within 2 minutes <!-- satisfied: timeout_cancel.rs, entry_amount refunded to each player -->\n- [x] No platform fee is deducted on any cancellation <!-- satisfied: cancel_match.rs and timeout_cancel.rs have no fee calculation -->\n- [x] Either player can trigger timeout cancel <!-- satisfied: timeout_cancel.rs caller == creator OR opponent -->\n\n### FR-5: Fairness Verification\n\nPlayers can verify the outcome of any completed match by inspecting the VRF inputs and recalculating the result.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Completed match displays VRF seed/proof details <!-- planned: MatchSettled event includes randomness bytes; Phase 2 adds vrf_request_key to event, verification UI reads Orao account -->\n- [ ] Players can independently verify the result matches the VRF output <!-- planned: Phase 2 verification.ts re-derives result from Orao randomness bytes via from_randomness -->\n- [ ] Verification is accessible from match history and result screen <!-- planned: Phase 2 verification UI accessible from ActiveMatchView + /fairness link -->\n\n### FR-6: Lobby Browser UI\n\nA browsable list of open coinflip matches with filtering and creation controls.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Open games list shows creator name/avatar, tier, wager amount, side, and join button <!-- satisfied: MatchCard.tsx:13 (PlayerAvatar:25, tier:50, amount:41, side:36, join:57) -->\n- [x] Filter by tier <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:43 matches.filter(m => m.tier === selectedTier) -->\n- [x] Sort by newest/oldest/amount <!-- satisfied: OpenMatchesList.tsx:18 sortMatches, :79 sort dropdown -->\n- [x] Create Game panel with tier selection grid and Heads/Tails toggle <!-- satisfied: CoinflipPage.tsx sidebar TierSelector + CoinSideSelector.tsx:19 -->\n- [ ] Estimated wait time shown (derived from recent match fill rate — deferred to post-MVP polish if data unavailable) <!-- deferred: self-deferred in criterion text, no match fill-rate data available -->\n\n### FR-7: Active Game and Result UI\n\nThe in-match view showing both players, coin flip animation, and result.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Both players shown with avatars, names, and wager amounts <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:88-108 PlayerAvatarCompact, side labels, entry amount -->\n- [x] 3D coin flip animation with multiple rotations and gradual slowdown <!-- satisfied: CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform (front/back faces :53-58), spinning classes :43-45 -->\n- [x] Winning side highlighted with glow effect <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:200-205 result color + textShadow glow -->\n- [x] \"YOU WIN!\" or \"YOU LOSE\" overlay displayed <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:128 \"You Won!\", :129-139 \"You Lost\" with heart+shards animation -->\n- [x] Payout amount shown for winner <!-- satisfied: ActiveMatchView.tsx:207-210 match.payoutAmount.toFixed(4) SOL -->\n- [ ] Quick rematch option available after result <!-- planned: Phase 2 rematch button in ActiveMatchView, reuses createMatch with same tier/side -->\n\n### FR-8: Audio Feedback\n\nSound effects accompany the coinflip experience.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Coin flip spinning sound during animation <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n- [ ] Dramatic pause before landing <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n- [ ] Victory sound for winner <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n- [ ] Coin clink on landing <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred (Scope Decisions) -->\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- A player can create a match, have it joined, see the flip, and receive payout in a single uninterrupted flow\n- Settlement correctness: winner always receives exactly (pool x 0.97), fee always reaches treasury\n- Any completed match can be independently verified for fairness\n- Match creation to resolution completes within 10 seconds of both players joining\n- Error states (insufficient balance, network failure, wallet disconnect) are clearly communicated\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Wallet connection via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (Privy removed)\n- Coinflip Anchor program (`solana/programs/coinflip`) with VRF provider (Orao, per `004-shared-infrastructure` spec)\n- Platform Anchor program (`solana/programs/platform`) for player profiles + fee config\n- `packages/anchor-client/` (generated from IDL via `scripts/sync-idl`)\n- Shared UI components (`packages/ui/`) for buttons, modals, cards, toasts\n- Dev environment: Anchor CLI 0.32.1, Solana CLI 2.3.13, Rust toolchain\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Tier amounts are fixed at the values defined in PLATFORM.md\n- Platform fee is 3% (300 bps). Confirmed in `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` §8. Split: 200 bps revenue, 70 bps rakeback, 30 bps chest treasury.\n- VRF provider: Orao (per `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md` FR-4). MagicBlock VRF dropped.\n- Non-custodial wallet flow via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (no Privy, no internal balance model)\n- Existing on-chain programs are legacy — coinflip will be rewritten against new shared crate + chosen VRF provider (see `004-shared-infrastructure` spec)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Match creation with tier + side | Create match via UI, verify lobby listing | Screenshot of lobby with new match |\n| 2 | Match joining assigns opposite side | Join match, verify side assignment | Screenshot showing both players |\n| 3 | VRF determines outcome | Inspect VRF output, verify determinism | VRF proof + recalculated result |\n| 4 | Winner payout = pool x 0.97 | Check on-chain settlement transaction | Explorer link showing amounts |\n| 5 | Platform fee reaches treasury | Check treasury PDA balance | Explorer link showing fee transfer |\n| 6 | Settlement is idempotent | Attempt double-settle, verify rejection | Error response or no-op proof |\n| 7 | Fairness verification works | Use verification UI to recalculate result | Screenshot of verification view |\n| 8 | End-to-end flow completes | Full playthrough from create to claim | Video or step-by-step screenshots |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n**Phase 1: Core Implementation (complete)**\n- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipConfig PDA + initialize_config instruction (done: TDD stubs commit)\n- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipMatch state + create_match instruction with tier validation + escrow (done: TDD stubs commit)\n- [x] [on-chain] Align shared crate tiers with spec: 6 tiers Iron→Diamond, amounts match 0.005→1.0 SOL (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement join_match — phase check, opponent != creator, escrow transfer, set LOCKED (done: iteration 2)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement resolve_match — oracle authority check, randomness→winner derivation (done: iteration 3; NOTE: deleted in 004 rewrite, replaced by claim-time VRF read)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement claim_payout — settlement, fee transfer, profile CPI, either-player trigger (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement cancel_match — WAITING-only, full refund + close (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [on-chain] Platform program scaffold — PlatformConfig + PlayerProfile + instructions (done: iteration 6)\n- [x] [on-chain] CPI from coinflip claim_payout → platform update_player_profile (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [engine] Create anchor-client package + sync-idl script (done: iteration 1, engine phase)\n- [x] [engine] Align game-engine with on-chain — types.ts side values, coinflip.ts PDA rewrite (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [frontend] Wire CoinflipContext to anchor-client — delete mock-simulation.ts, real chain calls (done: iteration 8)\n- [x] [frontend] Wire lobby browser + error handling (done: iteration 9)\n\n**Phase 1b: Shared Infrastructure Rewrite (complete — spec 004)**\n- [x] [on-chain] Orao VRF integration — join_match embeds VRF request, claim_payout reads randomness at claim time (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [on-chain] resolve_match deleted — 3-tx flow: create→join(+VRF)→claim(+settle) (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [on-chain] Shared crate modules: lifecycle, timeout, escrow, fees, pause, vrf_orao, commit_reveal, cpi (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [on-chain] timeout_cancel + force_close instructions (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [engine] IDL re-synced for rewritten programs (done: spec 004)\n- [x] [frontend] chain.ts rewritten for Orao VRF account structures (done: spec 004)\n\n**Phase 2: Data Consistency**\n- [x] [engine] Fix tier naming and amounts — in `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`: rename `Tier` union member `\"emerald\"` → `\"platinum\"`, update `TIER_AMOUNTS` values to SOL `{iron: 0.005, bronze: 0.01, silver: 0.1, gold: 0.25, platinum: 0.5, diamond: 1.0}`. Propagate `\"emerald\"` → `\"platinum\"` rename to ALL consumers across the monorepo (16 files reference \"emerald\" — use typecheck errors to find them all: `chain.ts`, `index.css`, boss-raid, lord-of-rngs, game-of-trades, crypto-crash, player-profile features). Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass across all packages. (done: iteration 10)\n- [ ] [frontend] Verify tier display correctness after amounts fix — confirm CoinflipPage TierSelector shows SOL values `{0.005, 0.01, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1.0}`, MatchCard displays correct wager amounts, `chain.ts` `entryAmountSol` reads correct values. Fix any hardcoded tier amount references that don't flow from `TIER_AMOUNTS`. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds for platform app.\n\n**Phase 2: Claimable Matches (G-1)**\n- [ ] [frontend] Add `fetchClaimableMatches(connection, playerPubkey)` to `features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — use `getProgramAccounts` with memcmp filters for matches where player is `creator` OR `opponent`, `claimed == false`, phase is non-terminal. Must handle both cases (player as creator and player as opponent are separate queries since the pubkey is at different offsets). Return `UIMatch[]`. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes.\n- [ ] [frontend] Surface claimable matches in CoinflipContext + CoinflipPage — add `claimableMatches: UIMatch[]` to context state, poll via `fetchClaimableMatches` alongside open matches. Show \"Your Matches\" section in CoinflipPage above the open lobby list with claim/cancel actions per match. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds.\n\n**Phase 2: Fairness Verification (FR-5)**\n- [ ] [on-chain] Add `vrf_request_key: Pubkey` field to `MatchSettled` event — in `solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` (event definition) and `claim_payout.rs` (emit site), add `vrf_request_key` from `coinflip_match.vrf_request_key`. This enables verification UIs to look up the Orao randomness account and confirm the randomness bytes are genuine VRF output. Verify: `anchor build -p coinflip` succeeds + all bankrun tests pass.\n- [ ] [engine] Re-sync IDL after MatchSettled event change — run `./scripts/sync-idl` to copy updated IDL + types into `packages/anchor-client/`. Verify anchor-client exports include `vrf_request_key` in MatchSettled event type. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes across monorepo.\n- [ ] [frontend] Build fairness verification utility — create `features/coinflip/utils/verification.ts`. Export `verifyMatch(connection, claimTxSignature): Promise<VerificationResult>`. Logic: (1) fetch parsed transaction by signature, (2) extract `MatchSettled` event from logs (parse program event data), (3) read `randomness` bytes from event, (4) re-derive result via `from_randomness(randomness[0])`, (5) compare derived winner to event `winner` field, (6) fetch Orao randomness account by `vrf_request_key` to confirm VRF fulfillment. Return `{verified, creator, opponent, winner, randomnessHex, derivedResult, vrfFulfilled}`. Verify: `pnpm typecheck` passes.\n- [ ] [frontend] Build fairness verification UI — add \"Verify Fairness\" button to ActiveMatchView (visible in completed phase). Opens a verification panel/modal showing: claim tx signature, VRF request key, raw randomness hex, derived result (Heads/Tails), recorded winner, verification status badge (Verified/Failed/Pending). Also wire the existing `/fairness` link in CoinflipPage to use this verification flow (user pastes a tx signature to verify any match). Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds.\n\n**Phase 2: Quick Rematch (FR-7.6)**\n- [ ] [frontend] Add rematch button to ActiveMatchView — visible when match phase is `complete`. Clicking calls `createMatch` with the same tier and the player's original side