{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KUNRXn6j17SkZ23U8YQECk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n     2→\n     3→// ============ Tier System ============\n     4→\n     5→export type Tier = \"iron\" | \"bronze\" | \"silver\" | \"gold\" | \"platinum\" | \"diamond\";\n     6→\n     7→export const TIER_VALUES: Record<Tier, number> = {\n     8→  iron: 0,\n     9→  bronze: 1,\n    10→  silver: 2,\n    11→  gold: 3,\n    12→  platinum: 4,\n    13→  diamond: 5,\n    14→};\n    15→\n    16→export const TIER_AMOUNTS: Record<Tier, number> = {\n    17→  iron: 0.005,\n    18→  bronze: 0.01,\n    19→  silver: 0.1,\n    20→  gold: 0.25,\n    21→  platinum: 0.5,\n    22→  diamond: 1.0,\n    23→};\n    24→\n    25→// ============ Pool State ============\n    26→\n    27→export type PoolPhase = \"waiting\" | \"locked\" | \"resolving\" | \"settled\" | \"cancelled\";\n    28→\n    29→export const POOL_PHASE_VALUES: Record<PoolPhase, number> = {\n    30→  waiting: 0,\n    31→  locked: 1,\n    32→  resolving: 2,\n    33→  settled: 3,\n    34→  cancelled: 4,\n    35→};\n    36→\n    37→export interface Pool {\n    38→  poolId: Uint8Array;\n    39→  gameId: string;\n    40→  roundId: number;\n    41→  tier: Tier;\n    42→  entryAmount: number;\n    43→  phase: PoolPhase;\n    44→  totalPool: number;\n    45→  playerCount: number;\n    46→  maxPlayers: number;\n    47→  createdAt: Date;\n    48→  lockedAt: Date | null;\n    49→  settledAt: Date | null;\n    50→  feeBps: number;\n    51→  vrfRequest: PublicKey | null;\n    52→  randomness: Uint8Array | null;\n    53→  winner: PublicKey | null;\n    54→  authority: PublicKey;\n    55→  treasury: PublicKey;\n    56→  carryoverAmount: number;\n    57→  carryoverFromRound: number;\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→// ============ Player Entry ============\n    61→\n    62→export type Side = \"none\" | \"green\" | \"red\";\n    63→\n    64→export const SIDE_VALUES: Record<Side, number> = {\n    65→  none: 0,\n    66→  green: 1,\n    67→  red: 2,\n    68→};\n    69→\n    70→export interface PlayerEntry {\n    71→  pool: PublicKey;\n    72→  player: PublicKey;\n    73→  amount: number;\n    74→  enteredAt: Date;\n    75→  sequence: number;\n    76→  side: Side;\n    77→  cashoutMultiplier: number | null;\n    78→  cashedOutAt: Date | null;\n    79→  claimed: boolean;\n    80→  payout: number;\n    81→  won: boolean;\n    82→  xpParticipation: number;\n    83→  xpWin: number;\n    84→}\n    85→\n    86→// ============ Game Config ============\n    87→\n    88→export interface GameConfig {\n    89→  gameId: string;\n    90→  paused: boolean;\n    91→  minBet: number;\n    92→  maxBet: number;\n    93→  feeBps: number;\n    94→  enabledTiers: Tier[];\n    95→  minPlayers: number;\n    96→  maxPlayers: number;\n    97→  roundDurationSecs: number;\n    98→  bettingWindowSecs: number;\n    99→  vrfQueue: PublicKey;\n   100→  authority: PublicKey;\n   101→  treasury: PublicKey;\n   102→  currentRound: number;\n   103→  totalRounds: number;\n   104→  totalVolume: number;\n   105→  totalFees: number;\n   106→  version: number;\n   107→  createdAt: Date;\n   108→  updatedAt: Date;\n   109→}\n   110→\n   111→// ============ Coinflip ============\n   112→\n   113→export type CoinSide = \"heads\" | \"tails\";\n   114→export type CoinflipPhase = \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"flipping\" | \"complete\";\n   115→\n   116→export const COIN_SIDE_VALUES: Record<CoinSide, number> = {\n   117→  heads: 0,\n   118→  tails: 1,\n   119→};\n   120→\n   121→export const COINFLIP_PHASE_VALUES: Record<CoinflipPhase, number> = {\n   122→  created: 0,\n   123→  ready: 1,\n   124→  flipping: 2,\n   125→  complete: 3,\n   126→};\n   127→\n   128→export interface CoinflipState {\n   129→  pool: PublicKey;\n   130→  player1: PublicKey;\n   131→  player2: PublicKey | null;\n   132→  player1Side: CoinSide;\n   133→  result: CoinSide | null;\n   134→  phase: CoinflipPhase;\n   135→  createdAt: Date;\n   136→  joinedAt: Date | null;\n   137→  flippedAt: Date | null;\n   138→  joinTimeoutSecs: number;\n   139→}\n   140→\n   141→export interface CoinflipMatch {\n   142→  pool: Pool;\n   143→  state: CoinflipState;\n   144→  player1Entry: PlayerEntry;\n   145→  player2Entry: PlayerEntry | null;\n   146→}\n   147→\n   148→// ============ Legacy Types (for backwards compatibility) ============\n   149→\n   150→/** @deprecated Use Pool instead */\n   151→export interface PoolState {\n   152→  roundId: string;\n   153→  gameId: string;\n   154→  tier: Tier;\n   155→  phase: \"waiting\" | \"betting\" | \"active\" | \"resolving\" | \"settled\";\n   156→  entries: LegacyPlayerEntry[];\n   157→  totalPool: number;\n   158→  createdAt: number;\n   159→  settledAt?: number;\n   160→  outcome?: unknown;\n   161→}\n   162→\n   163→/** @deprecated Use PlayerEntry instead */\n   164→export interface LegacyPlayerEntry {\n   165→  playerId: string;\n   166→  publicKey: string;\n   167→  tier: Tier;\n   168→  amount: number;\n   169→  timestamp: number;\n   170→  side?: \"green\" | \"red\";\n   171→  cashoutMultiplier?: number;\n   172→}\n   173→\n   174→// ============ Game IDs ============\n   175→\n   176→export const GAME_IDS = {\n   177→  COINFLIP: \"coinflip\",\n   178→  LORD_OF_RNGS: \"lord-of-rngs\",\n   179→  CRASH: \"crash\",\n   180→  CLOSE_CALL: \"close-call\",\n   181→  SLOTS: \"slots\",\n   182→  GAME_OF_TRADES: \"game-of-trades\",\n   183→  TUG_OF_EARN: \"tug-of-earn\",\n   184→  CHART_COURSE: \"chart-course\",\n   185→} as const;\n   186→\n   187→export type GameId = (typeof GAME_IDS)[keyof typeof GAME_IDS];\n   188→\n   189→// ============ XP System ============\n   190→\n   191→export const XP_BY_TIER: Record<Tier, { participation: number; win: number }> = {\n   192→  iron: { participation: 1, win: 3 },\n   193→  bronze: { participation: 1, win: 3 },\n   194→  silver: { participation: 10, win: 30 },\n   195→  gold: { participation: 25, win: 75 },\n   196→  platinum: { participation: 50, win: 150 },\n   197→  diamond: { participation: 100, win: 300 },\n   198→};\n   199→\n   200→// ============ Fee Constants ============\n   201→\n   202→export const FEE_CONSTANTS = {\n   203→  TOTAL_BPS: 300, // 3%\n   204→  PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS: 200, // 2.0%\n   205→  RAKEBACK_POOL_BPS: 70, // 0.7% — raid boss rewards\n   206→  CHEST_TREASURY_BPS: 30, // 0.3% — treasure chests\n   207→} as const;\n   208→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RRZb5ZUdRJYKbKfGnTAsmB","session_id":"394db446-9d72-42e7-88ec-8467376c4aa2","uuid":"044ee4dd-1a4a-4987-aa69-69e0a94ca14a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RRZb5ZUdRJYKbKfGnTAsmB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the files. Let me provide you with a comprehensive analysis of the tier display correctness for the coinflip game.\n\n## Tier Display Analysis - Full Contents Review\n\n### 1. **CoinflipPage.tsx** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx`)\n\n**Key findings:**\n- **Line 11**: Imports `TIER_AMOUNTS` from `@rng-utopia/game-engine/browser`\n- **Line 90-92**: Calculates potential payout: `selectedTier ? TIER_AMOUNTS[selectedTier] * 2 * 0.97 : 0`\n- **Line 144**: Displays Entry amount as `$${TIER_AMOUNTS[selectedTier]}` (direct lookup, uses SOL values as display)\n- **Line 149**: Displays Potential Payout as `$${potentialPayout.toFixed(2)}`\n- **Line 203**: Displays Entry from activeMatch as `$${activeMatch.entryAmount}`\n- **Line 207**: Displays Pot as `$${activeMatch.entryAmount * 2}`\n- **Line 371**: History modal displays Entry as `$${selectedHistoryMatch.entryAmount}`\n- **Line 376**: History modal displays Total Pot as `$${(selectedHistoryMatch.entryAmount * 2).toFixed(2)}`\n\n**Issue**: Uses `TIER_AMOUNTS[selectedTier]` which contains **SOL values** (0.005, 0.01, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1.0) and displays them directly with `$` prefix. These are SOL amounts, not USD.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **TierSelector.tsx** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/ui/src/layouts/TierSelector.tsx`)\n\n**Key findings:**\n- **Lines 7-14**: Defines `TIER_AMOUNTS` as SOL values:\n  ```typescript\n  iron: 0.005, bronze: 0.01, silver: 0.1, gold: 0.25, platinum: 0.5, diamond: 1.0\n  ```\n- **Line 17-24**: Defines `TIER_COLORS` for visual display\n- **Line 80**: Renders tier button with amount: `<span className=\"rng-tier-btn__amount\">{TIER_AMOUNTS[tier]}</span>`\n- **Issue**: Displays raw SOL values (e.g., \"0.005\") without a currency symbol\n\n---\n\n### 3. **MatchCard.tsx** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/components/MatchCard.tsx`)\n\n**Key findings:**\n- **Line 48**: Displays match amount as `{\"$\"}{match.entryAmount}`\n- **Issue**: Uses `match.entryAmount` which comes from the on-chain conversion (see chain.ts)\n- No hardcoded tier amounts here; all values flow from upstream\n\n---\n\n### 4. **chain.ts** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`)\n\n**Critical findings:**\n- **Line 11-16**: Imports `TIER_AMOUNTS` from `@rng-utopia/game-engine/browser`\n- **Line 136**: **`const entryAmountSol = TIER_AMOUNTS[tier];`** — Looks up the SOL value from TIER_AMOUNTS\n- **Line 137**: **`const totalPool = entryAmountSol * 2;`**\n- **Line 138**: **`const payoutAmount = totalPool * 0.97;`**\n- **Line 145**: Returns `entryAmount: entryAmountSol` in the UI match object\n\n**This is the conversion point**: The on-chain `OnChainMatch.entryAmount` (which is in lamports/native units from the smart contract) is **NOT used**. Instead, it's recalculated from `TIER_AMOUNTS[tier]` using the tier index. This assumes the on-chain contract enforces the exact SOL amounts.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **game-engine types.ts** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`)\n\n**Key findings:**\n- **Lines 16-23**: Defines `TIER_AMOUNTS` (same as in TierSelector):\n  ```typescript\n  iron: 0.005, bronze: 0.01, silver: 0.1, gold: 0.25, platinum: 0.5, diamond: 1.0\n  ```\n- **Lines 7-14**: Defines `TIER_VALUES` (enum indices for on-chain):\n  ```typescript\n  iron: 0, bronze: 1, silver: 2, gold: 3, platinum: 4, diamond: 5\n  ```\n- **Lines 200-207**: Fee constants (3% total)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Tier Display Flow\n\n```\nTIER_AMOUNTS (game-engine) [SOL values]\n    ↓\n    Used in CoinflipPage to display Entry (with $ prefix)\n    Used in TierSelector to display amount per button\n    Used in chain.ts onChainMatchToUI() to set entryAmount\n    ↓\nMatchCard.tsx displays match.entryAmount with $ prefix\n```\n\n---\n\n## Issues Identified\n\n| Issue | Location | Severity | Details |\n|-------|----------|----------|---------|\n| **Dollar sign on SOL amounts** | CoinflipPage.tsx (lines 144, 203, 207, 371, 376) | HIGH | Displays SOL values (0.005, 0.01, etc.) with `$` prefix, implying USD when they are actually SOL |\n| **No currency symbol in TierSelector** | TierSelector.tsx (line 80) | MEDIUM | Shows raw numbers like \"0.005\" without any currency indicator; should say \"0.005 SOL\" |\n| **Potential Payout calculation** | CoinflipPage.tsx (lines 90-92) | MEDIUM | Correctly multiplies by 2 and applies 0.97 fee, but displays as `$` which is misleading |\n| **match.entryAmount source** | chain.ts (line 136) | MEDIUM | Recalculates from `TIER_AMOUNTS[tier]` instead of using on-chain `data.entryAmount` — assumes contract enforces exact amounts |\n| **No SOL unit display** | All display locations | HIGH | Users see \"$0.005\" and \"$0.01\" but SOL is the actual unit; should be \"0.005 SOL\" or \"◎0.005\" |\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Add SOL unit to all displays** — Change `$${amount}` to `◎${amount}` or `${amount} SOL` across all files\n2. **Update TierSelector button** — Display \"0.005 SOL\" instead of just \"0.005\"\n3. **Verify on-chain enforcement** — Confirm the Coinflip program rejects transactions with tier amounts that don't match `TIER_AMOUNTS`\n4. **Consider display formatting** — Use consistent formatting (e.g., `◎0.005` is typical Solana convention)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aefcb61b7e5f902fd (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 45982\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 35295</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"394db446-9d72-42e7-88ec-8467376c4aa2","uuid":"028bbbb8-e39f-480d-bc0d-369731b10411","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to verify tier display correctness for a coinflip game. Please find and read the following fil